    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<h1>REMISSION OF SINS</h1><p>A King James Version phrase that carries the same meaning as &quot;forgiveness of sins.&quot; The New Testament uses a variety of terms to describe a single truth. Different expressions are used to describe the idea of forgiveness of sins:</p><ul><li><p>&quot;passing over&quot; in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:25\">Romans 3:25</a></p></li><li><p>&quot;covered&quot; in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:7\">Romans 4:7</a></p></li><li><p>&quot;not imputed&quot; in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:8\">Romans 4:8</a></p></li><li><p>&quot;remembered no more&quot; in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:17\">Hebrews 10:17</a></p></li></ul><p>One of the most significant ways of expressing forgiveness is the word &quot;remission&quot; (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:28\">Matthew 26:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:4\">Mark 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:77\">Luke 1:77</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:3\">3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:47\">24:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38\">Acts 2:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:43\">10:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:22\">Hebrews 9:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:18\">10:18</a>).</p><p>Remission has an interesting tradition in the Greek language. In a legal sense, remission meant dismissal from a job, release from an obligation, or cancellation of a debt or punishment. Over time, it came to mean amnesty or exemption from taxation. </p><p>In New Testament use, the activity of remission means &quot;to let go,&quot; &quot;to leave behind,&quot; or &quot;to send away.&quot; Because of this, the word is often translated into &quot;forgiveness&quot; as well as &quot;remission&quot; (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:31\">Acts 5:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:38\">13:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:18\">26:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">Ephesians 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:14\">Colossians 1:14</a>). While forgiveness can be exercised by both God and humans, the word &quot;remission&quot; almost always means forgiveness given by God (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:28\">Matthew 26:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:43\">Acts 10:43</a>).</p><p><em>See also</em> <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"4462\" data-resourceType=\"TyndaleBibleDictionary\">Forgiveness</span>.</p>",
